      "rationale": "Relevance of QoI at MRL 2 requires Gradation 2 (QoI directly maps to the clinical endpoint used in the regulatory decision). NIH and RHI are the standard hemolysis metrics used in FDA guidance for blood-contacting device evaluation. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 is the regulatory acceptance criterion per ASTM F1841. Gradation 3 achieved through additional sensitivity analysis demonstrating that NIH is monotonically sensitive to the geometric tolerance variations being evaluated, confirming it is the appropriate discriminating QoI for the COU.",
