    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Relevance of validation activities at MRL 2 requires Gradation 2 (validation experiments conducted on the same device class under conditions spanning the COU operating envelope). The FDA benchmark PIV dataset and in-vitro hemolysis experiments were conducted on the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under flow conditions (2–8 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) that bracket the 5 COU operating points. Blood analogue fluid properties match CPB conditions. Gradation 2 confirmed.",
